# Factor Backtest Skill

When the user asks to run a factor backtest, validate backtest inputs, inspect
backtest outputs, or explain the backtest behavior:

1. Read `.cursor/skills/factor-backtest/SKILL.md`.
2. Read `.cursor/skills/factor-backtest/references/backtest-contract.md`.
3. Do not edit `.cursor/skills/factor-backtest/scripts/backtest_engine/BackTest.py`
   unless the user explicitly asks for source-code changes.
4. For an explicit test-data run, use checked-in Yahoo-backed data under `.cursor/skills/factor-backtest/data/test_data`
   and run `python3 .cursor/skills/factor-backtest/scripts/run_factor_backtest.py --test-data`.
5. Treat the checked-in test data as a fixture only. For real backtests, the user
   must provide their own data; run `scripts/run_factor_backtest.py` with
   `--input-file`, `--factor-column`, and `--data-root`; omit `--output-dir` to
   use `output/run_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS/`.
6. Use `--report` only when the existing `scripts/factor_report_generate`
   Python modules and auxiliary datasets are available.
7. Treat the printed JSON summary as the run contract: verify `output_dir`, every
   file in `expected_outputs`, and `report_pdf` when `--report` is used.
8. Report generated files, key metrics from `stats.csv`, skipped optional report
   sections, and any missing-data or environment assumptions. Run
   `make_test_data.py` only when intentionally refreshing the saved Yahoo-backed
   test fixture; it requires network access.
